Server commands allow you to start and manage the [Temporal Server](/clusters#temporal-server) <span id="i-b838bf13-84ff-4f10-952b-4555ad02bdf3" class="clickable-i clickable-link-preview">ðŸ”—</span><div id="preview-modal-b838bf13-84ff-4f10-952b-4555ad02bdf3" class="preview-modal"><div class="modal-header"><div id="x-b838bf13-84ff-4f10-952b-4555ad02bdf3" class="clickable-x clickable-link-preview">x</div><b>Link preview</b></div><div class="preview-modal-title">What is the Temporal Server?</div><div class="preview-modal-description">The Temporal Server is a grouping of four horizontally scalable services.</div><div class="preview-modal-tags"><span class="preview-modal-tag">term</span> <span class="preview-modal-tag">explanation</span></div></div> from the command line.

Currently, `cli` server functionality extends to starting the Server.

## start-dev

The `temporal server start-dev` command starts the Temporal Server on `localhost:7233`.

The results of any command run on the Server can be viewed at http://localhost:7233.
